REVIEW QUESTIONS
----------------

1. Is direct base-reserve-edge-only the right Cajtucu V1 route policy, or should
   routed execution be introduced before paper-online?

2. Should Cajtucu own a richer ledger type before paper-online, including
   precision/lot/tick constraints and per-node reserve valuation history?

3. Should paper V1 keep one execution result per order, or should we already
   prepare for one order producing multiple fills?

4. Should buy-side partial fills remain per-asset, or should a future option
   scale all buy orders pro-rata when reserve is insufficient?

5. Is the updated synthetic direct-edge policy correct: default reject, with
   explicit research-replay opt-in when synthetic execution markets are needed?
